sentences: Booker Little Jr. (April 2, 1938 – October 5, 1961) was an American jazz trumpeter and composer.
In 1952, Little attended Manassas High School where he would begin his development on trumpet and later graduate.
After graduating, he moved to Chicago, Illinois to continue his studies at the Chicago Conservatory in 1954.
For about nine months, they both stayed at the YMCA where Rollins would influence Little greatly by encouraging him to find his own sound versus mimicking other musicians.
